## Difficulty

Intermediate

## Paper

4 square sheets (recommended: 15x15 cm or larger)

## Instructions

This diagram is divided into sections to simplify the construction process:

### Initial Setup

Each Tangram piece is constructed individually. Use four square sheets to create all seven pieces. Fold each sheet and cut along the indicated lines.

### Piece A (make 2)

Fold the paper following the diagram and tuck the final flap into the pocket to lock the shape.

### Piece B (make 2)

Repeat the same steps as Piece A using a smaller square template derived from Piece B.

### Piece C

Follow the sequence of folds and insert the final section into the pocket to secure the shape.

### Piece D

This piece includes a reverse fold step. Follow carefully and lock the structure by inserting into the pocket.

### Piece E

Complete the final folds and insert the flap into the pocket to finish the piece.

---

## Key Features

```
- Uses 4 square sheets for improved accuracy
- All 7 traditional Tangram pieces included
- Clean geometric construction
- No measurements required
- Beginner-friendly folding sequence
```

